                                                                <customfield id="customfield_12310192" key="com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:textarea">
                        <customfieldname>Release Note</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>This JIRA allows to run shell commands from within grun by using new sh command which has the following format:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
sh &amp;lt;shell command to run&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
For instance, the command below will allow you to run ls command on the location from which you started pig:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
grunt&amp;gt; sh ls&lt;br/&gt;
bigdata.conf&lt;br/&gt;
nightly.conf&lt;br/&gt;
.....&lt;br/&gt;
grunt&amp;gt;</customfieldvalue>

                        </customfieldvalues>
                    </customfield>
